A 26-year-old househelp was charged in a Kibera court yesterday with pouring hot water on her employer's cousin.Elizabeth Okutoi appeared before senior principal Magistrate Elizabeth Juma and denied assaulting the Sudanese.The court heard that on December 19 this year at River Run Apartments on Riara Road in Nairobi, she assaulted David Atem.Okutai asked for reasonable bond terms.In her ruling, Juma ordered her to pay a Sh 10,000 bond or a cash bail of the same amount and she also directed the prosecution to supply her with copies of all witness statements that will be used in the trial.The case was set for hearing on March 2 next year.